<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Lorenz_curve&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.eldis.org/static/DOC2910.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.eldis.org/static/DOC2910.htm" rel="nofollow">Measuring income inequality: a new database</a>, with link to dataset</li>
<li><a href="http://www.wessa.net/co.wasp" class="external text" title="http://www.wessa.net/co.wasp" rel="nofollow">Free Online Software (Calculator)</a> computes the Gini Coefficient, plots the Lorenz curve, and computes many other measures of concentration for any dataset</li>
<li>Free Calculator: <a href="http://www.poorcity.richcity.org/calculator.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.poorcity.richcity.org/calculator.htm" rel="nofollow">Online</a> and <a href="http://luaforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=49" class="external text" title="http://luaforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=49" rel="nofollow">downloadable scripts</a> (<a href="/wiki/Python_(programming_language)" title="Python (programming language)">Python</a> and <a href="/wiki/Lua_programming_language" title="Lua programming language" class="mw-redirect">Lua</a>) for Atkinson, Gini, and Hoover inequalities</li>
<li>Users of the <a href="http://www.r-project.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.r-project.org/" rel="nofollow">R</a> data analysis software can install the "ineq" package which allows for computation of a variety of inequality indices including Gini, Atkinson, Theil.</li>
<li>A <a href="http://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/loadFile.do?objectId=19968" class="external text" title="http://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/loadFile.do?objectId=19968" rel="nofollow">MATLAB Inequality Package</a>, including code for computing Gini, Atkinson, Theil indexes and for plotting the Lorenz Curve. Many examples are available.</li>
</ul>


